This datapack aims to add composting mechanics to all vanilla items which [i]should[/i] be compostable, being as close as possible to vanilla mechanics.

[h2]Features[/h2]New compostable items, including rotten flesh, poisonous potatoes, foods, and many more (see the list below). These new items are compostable in the following ways:
[list]
[*]By putting them in a hopper on top of a composter, the same way you would do with vanilla-compostable items.[/*]
[/list][center][img title="Composting a poisonous potato via hopper" width=480 height=270]https://github.com/daenvil/more_compostable_items/blob/main/.wiki_assets/screenshots/hopper.gif?raw=true[/img][/center][list]
[*]By dropping them [i]inside[/i] a composter (vanilla items are also given this feature).[/*]
[/list][center][img title="Composting a poisonous potato via hopper" width=480 height=270]https://github.com/daenvil/more_compostable_items/blob/main/.wiki_assets/screenshots/dropping.gif?raw=true[/img][/center]
[i]Note: composting items by dropping them inside composters can be disabled (see the "Available commands" section)[/i]

[style b color=#e74c3c]WARNING:[/style] Custom-composting only works with composters that are placed by players. This means that it wont work with world-generated composters, with composters summoned via commands, or with composters placed [i]before[/i] the datapack was installed. Simply [b]break a composter and place it again manually to make the datapack register it[/b].

