[h2]Other info:[/h2]
[spoiler=Customization]This datapack provides item tags for 10%, 30%, 50%, 65%, 85%, and 100% composting chances. You can find their .json files in [i]<this datapack>/data/dnv.recyclecraft/tags/items/[/i]. If you want to customize the datapack for your own use, edit those files however you want (simply add/remove any item you want in those lists and it will become compostable/uncompostable).

Warning: there is another item tag for vanilla-compostable items, do not edit that one unless you know what you are doing. It is used to detect when a hopper is containing them as to not overlap vanilla-composting with custom-composting, otherwise, both mechanics would function at the same time, breaking the intended effect of this datapack.[/spoiler]
[spoiler=Available commands]There are some commands that you can optionally use with this datapack:

- "[color=#18a085]/function dnv.compost:dropping_toggle[/color]": enables or disables compost-by-dropping ([b]on[/b] by default). Disable it if you don't want compostable items that drop inside a composter to be composted.
- "[color=#18a085]/function dnv.compost:uninstall[/color]": removes all the entities and scoreboard objectives created by this datapack. Run this function if you want to stop using the datapack to ensure it leaves no trace. All composter markers will be removed, meaning that if you want to use the datapack again after uninstalling it, you will have to manually replace already existing composters in order for the datapack to register them again.[/spoiler]
